description:
First story is prequel to Chrysalis. Second story "Chrysalis" is separated into 4 different stories, 1st one was in Cybrid #1, last three of them were in Asylum volume.

Chrysalis, Part 1: Dysfunctional Families.
Chrysalis, Part 2: All I Need To Know, I Learned From An Assassin!
Chrysalis, Part 3: Loyalty
Chrysalis, Part 4: Resurrection
 
To be continued in Avengelyne vol2 #4
name: Cybrid; Chrysalis

description: The tale of Avengeblade's origins as she is created and sent out on her first mission, to destroy The Bad Girls Club! A group of slutty female characters parodying real comic book characters.
name: Cutting Edge Parody

description: Avengeblade descends on Westsquall Comics the home of Homogenized Studios to tackle the plethora of generic teen super heroes in this satire on the comic industries current fad for "Gen Ex" clones.
name: Avengeblade

description: Kicking off an all-new miniseries bringing you two “classic” silver-age tales of the Sentry at the birth of the Marvel Age! When the Golden Guardian is critically injured, Scout, Lindy Lee and Watchdog have to travel back in time to learn exactly how Rob Reynolds became THE SENTRY. They must learn the secrets to save our hero – so he can save the world! PLUS: When the Tinkerer and the Mad Thinker team up to create a device capable of stealing the Sentry's powers, they only have one obstacle on their path to world domination. The parasitic beam takes HOURS to work! What evil scheme will keep the Sentry in place long enough to destroy him? Don't miss the breathtaking tale of monsters and mayhem!
name: The Secret Origin of The Sentry

description: Continuing the most exciting and comprehensive Marvel Handbook ever assembled! This twelve-volume guide to the Marvel Universe features more than 100 huge entries in each tome! This issue - from Crimson Dynamo (Gennady Gavrilov) to the Elements of Doom! Spotlighting people (Crystal, Cyclops, Daredevil, Dazzler, Deadpool, three Deathloks, three Death's Heads, Dr. Doom, Dr. Octopus, Dr. Strange, Domino, Dracula, Drax, Dust, Echo, Elektra), places (the Daily Bugle, District X), teams (the Defenders), species (Demons, Deviants), alternate realities (Days of Future Past, Earth-A, Earth X) items (the Darkhold) and more!
name: Volume 3

  2. "Assault on Kastle Vertigo!" (Green Arrow vs. Count Vertigo) written by Bob Haney, penciled by Trevor Von Eeden, inked by Larry Mahlstedt, colored by Carl Gafford and lettered by Todd Klein.
  3. "No Title" (Plastic Man) written by Martin Pasko, penciled by Joe Staton, inked by Bob Smith, colored by Adrienne Roy and lettered by John Costanza.

  9. "Hembeck" by Fred Hembeck.

The annual Justice League of America and Justice Society of America team up continues in Justice League of America #196. The Top battles the Flash in The Flash #303. And, finally "Direct Currents".

  • 48 pages no ads.
  • Justice League Satellite and the Flash cameo appearance in the Superman-Batman story.
  • Rope Arrow used.
  • Lord Insectus, Shadow Thief and Thangarians cameo flashback appearances in the Hawkman story.
name: In the Citadel of the Weapon Master / Assault on Kastle Vertigo! / No Title / Victory? / Sivana's Nobel!

1. Get Out of My Life Superman! (Lois Lane, Superman, Jimmy Olsen, Perry White, Lana Lang, Lucy Lane / written by Leo Dorfman : reprinted from: Superman's Girlfriend, Lois Lane #80)

Story comes in 3 parts:

part 1. Get Out of My Life Superman!

part 2. Love Comes to Lois Lane

part 3. The Jealous Superman

2. No Witnesses in Outer Space (Lois Lane, Superman, Jimmy Olsen (flashback), Lana Lang (flashback) / written by Leo Dorfman : reprinted from: Superman's Girlfriend, Lois Lane #81)

Story comes in 2 parts:

part 1. No Witnesses in Outer Space

part 2. Lois Lane's Extreme Space Peril

description: The Eisner-nominated adventures continues! June, 1943 - control of the Mediterranean hangs in the balance as the Allied Invasion of Sicily crashes against elite Nazi soldiers in "walking tank" armor that only Atomic Robo can stop! Too bad he's battered, beaten, shot, hit with grenades, captured, and miles away. What does this mean for the Allies who are trapped between the sea and these unstoppable Nazi super weapons?
name: And Then There's the Robots

description: Michael Turner's Fathom makes its triumphant return for the thrilling third volume! The deadly tides of change rise above the surface in the exciting third chapter of the best selling action adventure series, Fathom! Humankind faces a new threat to their existence from the ancient and powerful underwater race, the Black, while the return of the villainous Killian sends shockwaves throughout the already-devastated world of the Blue. Meanwhile, Aspen Matthews attempts to adjust to life above the water, but a future - and past - threat emerges to disrupt her safe haven!
name: Changing Currents

description:
Overview:

Death and destruction have risen above the surface behind the wrath of Killian and Kiani's bloody vengeance! With the aftermath of their attack on a historic American location sending ripples across the oceans and beneath, any hope for peace between the Humans and the Blue is completely lost as a new threat has emerged to lead the human invasion. Meanwhile, Aspen makes her return below the surface to Muria with Cannon and Chance, and encounters the Blue's special... guest! The deadly tides of change rise above the surface as the exciting third volume of the best-selling action adventure series, Fathom, continues! Available with covers from Ale Garza and Michael Gunnell.
name: Floodgates

description:
Overview:

Billy learns that there is a new kid at school - good luck making friends! Theo Adam has magically returned from banishment, and in the process he's completely forgotten the magic word that changes him into Black Adam! What he does know is that Billy has the same power, so he's going to do everything he can to get the secret word out of Billy - even if it means joining Billy's school and playing nice.

volume.name: Billy Batson and the Magic of SHAZAM!

description: Lord Burnham and the cannibalistic war mage Mako have joined forces to hunt for the legendary Laughing Magician. But first, they must find John Constantine, who is himself about to realize that he finally may have met his match.
name: The Roots Of Coincidence, Part 1

description: Beginning an all-new arc that looks at two of the rez's most intriguing inhabitants. Chief Red Crow sits atop an empire amassed through murder and intimidation, but will the death of a friend make him change his ways? Dino Poor Bear is a young kid just scraping by, hoping to make a better life for himself, but how far is he willing to go to get what he wants?
name: The Gravel in Your Guts, Part One

description:
Features Include:
Bloody Talons Of The Feathered Fiends!
Kioto, the Mad Jap!
Alibi For Grim Deceit!
Battles the Terror of Triple Destruction!
name: Bloody Talons Of The Feathered Fiends!
Gone But Not Forgotten

description:
Champ!

A great war story filled with macho sentimentality about a failed boxer (who could have been a champ) who takes on a Nazi tank and becomes a true champ. This one has cool dialog like: "Nazi steel will cool off the fool!" and a main character who hauls and fires machine gun all by himself while smoking a cigarette.

Second Best

This story has an interesting premise about an American soldier and his German-born nemesis from college who works as a Nazi infiltator.

A Letter From Joe

A story about what really happens in war and what the boys write home about.

Survival For Shorty

A story about a marine who has to overcome the enemy and his own height.
name: Champ

description:
Patrol!

There's nothing to it...It's as harmless as sticking your head into a lion's mouth when the lion hasn't eaten in a month!

This first story revolves around a USMC combat patrol.

No Exit!

In a small village behind enemy lines, an ex-motorcycle stunt rider and his partner are put to the rockiest test! For the enemy's sneak punch was timed to smash the American advance -- and it was cycle skill against Panzer power as the team battled to escape the town for which there was no exit!

Lucky Charm!

A man in combat must have something to cling to...something that gives him the faith to go on. It can be many things. A memory, a letter from home, a picture...But with PVT Roy Brown It was a Lucky Charm!

Frightened Hero!

Perry Walters had been pushed around all his life -- and consequently never arrive anywhere on time! But this time, death waited to tag anyone who was late!
name: Patrol

description:
Overview
The sleepy little town of Moorehigh is about to wake up to its worst nightmare: Evan Rendell, aka Dr. Giggles, is coming home to settle some old scores. Adapted from writer/director Manny Coto's script by Steven Grant and artists Kent Burles and Alan J. Burrows. Covers by Doug Mahnke (The Mask).

Overview
The sleepy little town of Moorehigh is about to wake up to its worst nightmare: Evan Rendell, aka Dr. Giggles, is coming home to settle some old scores. Adapted from writer/director Manny Coto's script by Steven Grant and artists Kent Burles and Alan J. Burrows. Covers by Doug Mahnke (The Mask).

Fans of Mike Allred's Madman will be happy to know that Dr. Robot, the delightful comic strip by Bernie Mireault, creator of The Jam, will be reprinted in a special issue featuring all four color strips that originally appeared in Madman along with some new never-before-seen artwork. Follow the giant happy robot as he fights monsters, falls in love, and faces off against other giant robots.

Overview
In the year 4077, Ledomiam, the last of the free nations, has reluctantly agreed to make peace with the Romunilian Empire. Karula Olzen, second daughter of the Ledomiam royal family, has been sent to the Romunilian capital to sign a so-called Treaty of Amity, a document which would reduce her country to little more than a vassal state. But, once on the other side of enemy lines, peace is the last thing on Karula's mind.
name: Rise of the Dragon Princess (Part 1 of 6)

description: When the Foolkiller targets a hate-crime group known as the White Angels, a secret society whose arteries snake from the back alleys to the Hollywood hills, he crosses paths with the Punisher. Sound like the recipe for trouble? Normally yes, but this particular plate of vengeance just might be big enough to share.
name: Part 3: Fool's Gold

description: Lisa needs a little one-on-one time with Marge. But, during their afternoon skate-date in the park, Marge displays her fast-breaking and bone-crunching moves on an unsuspecting purse snatcher, and as fast as you can turn the page, Marge becomes Springfield's new Roller Derby Queen - leaving Lisa behind to eat her dust! There's a new derby diva in town this September!
name: A Skate With Destiny!

description: Meet the Imperial Guardsmen of Blazer Company, garrisoned in a tactical position known with typical soldier's irony as Paradise City. As the Tau attack, the regiment's famed Hellhound tanks fry Tau warriors and mortars drop explosive shells on their heads. In the midst of the battle, the fate of war could tip in the Imperial forces' favor - or tip towards betrayal and annihilation!

name: Tangent: Superman's Reign, Chapter Three; History Lesson, Chapter Three
Tangent: Superman's Reign, Chapter Two; History Lesson, Chapter Two
Tangent: Superman's Reign, Chapter One; History Lesson, Chapter One

description:
Overview

The assembled Autobots take center stage as the mystery surrounding the Decepticons’ sudden–and demonstrative–change ofmodus operandi deepens. Can Ratchet convince Prowl that drastic action needs to taken now, not later, action that involves a certain Optimus Prime? If not, well, it may be that Ratchet has to take some (more!) drastic action of his own. As for the Decepticons, they’re already braced for a response, Autobot or otherwise, and the first order of business… is to wipe out all remaining evidence!
name: Infiltration Part 3

description:
Overview

Ratchet needs answers, before the crisis on Earth escalates, and that means sending a crack team deep—literally—into enemy territory. Too bad then, given Ratchet’s oath to protect human life, that his available resources amount to Verity, Hunter and Jimmy. Too bad also that Decepticon unit commander Starscream is intent on removing all evidence of his indiscretions, and that includes the particular bit of ‘enemy territory’ in question. Enter: Blitzwing and Skywarp!
name: Infiltration Part 4

description:
Multiple 4 Stories in this Issue:


  • The Seven Sons of Satan     (guest-starring: Captain America)

  • Frozen Death (guest-starring: Captain America)

  • Flaming Steel! (guest-starring: The Human Torch)

    Story: The Blackout Murder Case (1 page)
name: The Chambers of Dr. Agony

description:
Overview

In a reckless bid to right one of his many past wrongs, Cade Skywalker has become a prisoner of the Sith. It’s a banner day for Emperor Darth Krayt, who hopes that Skywalker’s abilities will complete Krayt’s longtime quest to restore his own power.

But the other Sith are less certain of their Master’s motives. And there are others within the Empire who would rather see Cade dead than a pawn of the Emperor.

And Cade himself is none too happy about his situation. But what can he do? He turned his back on every friend who might come to his aid. He’s made bad choices, and now he has to live—or die—with them!

This issue reveals the identity of Darth Krayt!
name: Claws of the Dragon, Part Two

description:
Overview

This is it–the one you’ve been waiting for! Megatron arrives on Earth, and he’s not in the best of moods. His local Decepticon infiltration unit has broken protocol and gone rogue, and he’s not about to take it lying down. Once he’s got the whys and wherefores, there’ll be due punishment meted out, starting with Skywarp and Blitzwing. What about the Autobots and their human allies? Well, they’re all (wisely) staying well out of harm’s way. All, that is, except for Verity Carlo, who’s set for her own, personal face-to-face with Megatron!
name: Infiltration Part 5

description: The first titanic arc—Infiltration—wraps up in spectacular, no-holds-barred style, as Megatron sets about—demonstrably—putting his house (on Earth) in order. But, mighty as he is, has even Megatron got what it takes to curtail the activities of the all-new, hyper-powered Starscream? Whichever way it goes, the outlook looks distinctly bleak for the beleaguered earthbound Autobots. Could be that it’s time for Prowl and Co. to roll out the big guns?
name: Infiltration Part 6

description: For those of you craving unchecked, cover-to-cover giant robot action (guaranteed no humans!) on an epic scale, look no further than this special space epic. So far, in “Infiltration,” we’ve had tantalizing hints about the state of play elsewhere in the TRANSFORMERS universe, but now we look in on Cybertron itself, unlocking a dark, dark chapter in the planet’s history, one that is about to hit the Autobots and Decepticons again… full force! By the Beast Wars team supreme of Simon Furman and Don Figueroa.
name: Stormbringer Part 1

description:
Tooth Delay: Dexter has to visit the dentist to get acavity filled, unless of course he can escape first.

Up a Tree: Dexter and Mandark try to get Lee-Lee's cat out of a tree.
name: Tooth Delay Up A Tree

description:
1. "Greater Love Hath No Man...!" (Superman and Batman) written by Cary Burkett, penciled by Adrian Gonzales, inked by Brett Breeding, colored by Gene D'Angelo and lettered by Todd Klein.
  2. "...The Archer or the Man?" (Green Arrow and Black Canary) written by Mike W. Barr, penciled by Trevor Von Eeden, inked by Larry Mahlstedt, colored by Thomas J. Ziuko and lettered by John Costanza.
  3. "The Song the Shrieker Sang" (Zatanna) written by Gerry Conway, penciled by Gene Colan, inked by Bob Smith, colored by Adrienne Roy and lettered by Milt Snapinn.
  4. "Gone with the Wings!" (Hawkman and Hawkgirl) written by Bob Rozakis, penciled by Alex Saviuk, inked by Rodin Rodriguez, colored by Carl Gafford and lettered by P. Bernard Jr.
  5. "Silence, Please" (Captain Marvel) written by E. Nelson Bridwell, penciled by Don Newton, inked by Larry Mahlstedt, colored by Adrienne Roy and lettered by Pierre Bernard Jr.
  6. "DC Profile #82 - Denis Jensen" by Michael C. Carmichael.
  7. "Daily Planet" Volume 81 Issue 13 for the month of September 1981 edited by Bob Rozakis, production by Jodi Saviuk and lettered by Typeset. Featuring a DC and Marvel team up of Batman meets the Incredible Hulk in DC Special Series #27. Plus, more exciting adventures with Dial 'H' for Hero in Adventure Comics #488. Roy Thomas will be taking over the writing duties for Wonder Woman but don't miss the action by Robert Kanigher in Wonder Woman #286. And, finally "Direct Currents".
  8. "Hembeck" by Fred Hembeck.

Notes:

  • 48 pages no ads.
  • Knockout Gas Arrow, Boomerang Arrow and Grappling Hook Arrow used.
  • Green Arrow story is dedicated to Denny O'Neil.
  • Superman and Green Lantern cameo appearances in the Hawkman story.
name: Greater Love Hath No Man...! / ...The Archer or the Man? / The Song the Shrieker Sang / Gone with the Wings! / Silence, Please

description:
Overview
The best-laid plans of mice and royalty . . . ! Princess Karula's attempted assassination of Gustav, ruler of the Romunilian empire, has gone sour, and now she is trapped behind enemy lines with only a small band of her planet's army to protect her. The next move belongs to Gustav, and he isn't known for playing games.
name: Rise of the Dragon Princess (Part 2 of 6)

description:
Overview
A mysterious and buxom swordswoman clad only in chain mail and charm has chopped her way through her competition. Now she has another taker -- Dard, the hot headed, hard drinking, womanizing commander of the Royal Border Patrol. He has designs on besting her at battle and then besting her in bed; and she has designs on subverting his forces. Though all may be fair at love and war, this pair is pushing the envelope!
name: Rise of the Dragon Princess (Part 3 of 6)

description:
Overview
She bested him in battle -- defeated him in a swordfight -- and that should have sent him packing. But he's Dard, the hotheaded, hard-drinking, womanizing commander of the Royal Border Patrol; and she's Karula, the beautiful, buxom, sword-wielding princess of Ledomiam. And so the battle in the bar has become a war of the sexes -- and the next battleground is Karula's shower! Grab a towel and shed your shirt, 'cause it's about to get hot and steamy!
name: Rise of the Dragon Princess (Part 4 of 6)

description:
Overview
As leader of the Royal Border Patrol, Dard has taken plenty of bullets and other assorted wounds in the line of duty. It was exactly that which prepared him for saving the buxom, sword-wielding princess Karula from the Bosvanian army. But when Karula catches him with his own personal harem . . . well, nothing could have prepared him to survive that onslaught!
name: Rise of the Dragon Princess (Part 5 of 6)

description:
Overview
The sexy swordswoman Karula's equally-buxom sister, Queen Rosalia, is held captive by the Bosvanians! Karula's charmed an entire army into following her into the fray, but it's going to take more than a little cleavage and a lot of cleavers to walk out of this one alive -- there's a kamikaze squadron coming to blow them all to smithereens!
name: Rise of the Dragon Princess (Part 6 of 6)

description:
Overview
Her country's being threatened by the empire-building Bosvanians, her curvaceous, buxom body boils with the blood of a warrior, and now she has a mystical sword that can cut a path through the enemy! The series may be called The Revenge of Gustav, but you can bet that fire-eyed fighter named Karula is going to come out on top!
name: The Revenge of Gustav (Part 1 of 6)

description:
Overview
They're bound, gagged, and nude! They're the women of a nearby farm town, and it's up to the curvaceous warrior Karula to free them! Armed with her mystical sword, she heads into the fray against the entire Bosvanian army -- and she's coming back a winner, or a corpse!
name: The Revenge of Gustav (Part 2 of 6)

description:
Overview
All men lust after the sexy, curvaceous body of the warrior princess Karula! But possessed by the mystical sword of Kurrg, all Karula lusts after is blood, and she's gonna spill it by the bucket in the Imperial city of Makkas, in a bar crowded with Imperial soldiers!
name: The Revenge of Gustav (Part 3 of 6)

description: The Avengers want a new member and they have their eyes on Luke Cage. But Luke is not interested in joining a team, he prefers the solo style. Will the Avengers be able to convince him to join up, or will he follow the solo road?
name: Power, Man.

description: In part two of this cosmic epic from Furman and Figueroa, captives of a mysterious cult worship the once and former “weapon of mass destruction” known as THUNDERWING, while OPTIMUS PRIME—the memory of the insane, tormented Decepticon scientist’s last near-apocalyptic rampage still uppermost in his anguished memory—unleashes his own last resort solution—the WRECKERS!
name: Stormbringer Part 2

description:
Final part of Judge Dredd - Mutie Block. As tensions rise between norms and muties it's down to Dredd to keep the peace and diffuse tensions before all-out block war erupts across the Meg.

Cover: Clint Langley (A.B.C. Warriors)

  • Judge Dredd - Mutie Block (part 4 - final part) (John Wagner - Kev Walker)
  • The Red Seas - Old Gods (part 4) (Ian Edginton - Steve Yeowell)
  • A.B.C. Warriors - The Volgan War - Book Three (part 3) (Pat Mills - Clint Langley)
  • Stalag 666 (part 4) (Tony Lee - Jon Davis-Hunt)
  • Lobster Random - The Forget-Me-Knot (part 3) (Simon Spurrier - Carl Critchlow)
name: Prog 1603

description: The stunning conclusion! After an explosive showdown of thunder and lightning on the battlefield, Hercules and his companions are set to end Egypt's civil war. But even with a cunning plan to defeat Khadis, Lord of Lightning and the insurgent king Amenmessu, there still remains a traitor in the royal house of Seti II - and when the dust has settled on the grounds of war, Hercules will not rest until the spy pays for his or her crimes against the sovereign of Egypt! Featuring two different covers from Clint Langley.
name: The Thracian Wars, Part 5

description: The action explodes on two fronts, as—on CYBERTON—the WRECKERS kick back (hard!) against BLUDGEON’s rogue cult, and—on Nebulos—THUNDERWING shows exactly why, last time around, it took the combined firepower of two armies just to put him on ‘pause.’ As events spiral out of control and the body count rises, MEGATRON prepares to execute his distinctly terminal no-win scenario.
name: Stormbringer Part 3

description:
Multiple 4 Stories in this Issues



Castle of Doom (featuring Captain America and Bucky)

Murder For Profit (featuring the Human Torch and Toro)

Frozen Death (featuring Captain America and Bucky)

Peril of the Past (featuring Captain America and Bucky)
name: Castle of Doom

description: The Queen of Spades has siezed the Queen of Hearts, but Mary-Ann cuts them both down & then refuses to be the new queen. The Cheshire cat takes the throne & reaks havoc on Wonderland until the Dutchess forces him to step down. Having lost his home, the White Rabbit is forced to live with his maid in the Slowsand lands & Wonderland is left in a blissful state of anarchy.

1. "General Scarr's Army of Crime!" (Superman and Batman) written by Cary Burkett, penciled by Rich Buckler, inked by Bob Smith, colored by Carl Gafford and lettered by Ben Oda.
  2. "Harmony and Discord" (Green Arrow) written by Joey Cavalieri, penciled by Trevor Von Eeden, inked by Larry Malhstedt, colored by Tom Ziuko and lettered by Philip Felix.
  3. "Now You Czemm... Now You Don't!" (Hawkman) written by Bob Rozakis, penciled by Alex Saviuk, inked by Frank Chiaramonte, colored by Jerry Serpe and lettered by Janice Chiang.
  4. "The Secret of the Freeman Brothers!" (Captain Marvel, Captain Marvel Jr., Mary Marvel and Kid Eternity) written by E. Nelson Bridwell, penciled by Don Newton, inked by Frank Chiaramonte, colored by Adrienne Roy and lettered by Ben Oda.

Notes:

  • Rope Arrow and Gas Emitting Arrow used.
  • Mavis Trent, Superman, Hawkwoman, Matter-Master, John Small, Shadow-Thief and Hyanthis cameo hallucination appearances in the Hawkman story.
  • Captain Marvel Jr. and Kid Eternity origins retold.
  • Mr. Mind cameo appearance.
name: General Scarr's Army of Crime! / Harmony and Discord / Now You Czemm... Now You Don't! / The Secret of the Freeman Brothers!
